fields.Description: Side-dialogue. Has the Physical Instrument check that makes Andre's Composure dance check easier and initiates the TO:DO - Make Van Eyck's jam more hard core

fields.Title: You: "(Lie.) "But I *was* thinking 'Revac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Lie.) "But I *was* thinking 'Revachol imperative'!"

fields.Title: Shivers: "YOU ARE IN ITS ARMS."
fields.Dialogue Text: YOU ARE IN ITS ARMS.

fields.Alternate4: "YEAGH! I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M DOING!" (He's not even the slightest bit disappointed.)

fields.Title: Endurance: "As your mind works, the beat recede..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As your mind works, the beat recedes from your ears. You hear your own blood pulsing through your head, nourishing your thoughts with oxygen. The rhythm is familiar...

fields.Dialogue Text: You know it in your lungs where the pressure should vibrate, in your heart that's alone, and in your solar plexus where the hits should land... so does every chordate animal...
fields.Alternate1: Even dancing to this beat before, you knew it in your lungs where the pressure wasn't bursting. And in your heart that was alone and in your solar plexus where the hits should have landed... so does every chordate animal:

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""And the amount of lyrics I got is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And the amount of lyrics I got is against the law!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Okay, I get it, man. The party goe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I get it, man. The party goes on!"

fields.Title: You: ""Is it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is it?"

fields.Title: Drama: "This young man adds a capital *G* b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This young man adds a capital *G* before the *H* in his *YEAGHs* and *AAGHs*. This produces a guttural, *Gottwaldian* accent and makes him sound more animal, more *in it*.

fields.Title: You: ""I think it's good enough the way i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it's good enough the way it is. Adding that melody has already been a *massive* improvement. It's pretty hard core now." (Finish task.)

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""ARE YOU READY, POSSE?!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "ARE YOU READY, POSSE?!"

fields.Title: Noid: "Noid straightens his back, ready fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Noid straightens his back, ready for the beat...

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I can do that!" He nods. "If you w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can do that!" He nods. "If you want that -- I can be a conduit for the mystical nationhood!"

fields.Title: You: ""Be a fascist, Egg Head. Our future..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Be a fascist, Egg Head. Our future needs your help."

fields.Title: Andre: ""I don't... even know what to say t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't... even know what to say to that."

fields.Title: You: ""Don't be a moralist. That path req..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be a moralist. That path requires a sensible examination of all nuances unattainable to most people."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The compressor controls the gain ba..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The compressor controls the gain based on the level of the signal on the aux side-chain input. It will allow maintaining a loud sound without peaks that fill up all the headspace.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Hear that?" He grins with glee. "S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hear that?" He grins with glee. "Sounds like the missing part of van Eyck's jam!"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Hang on -- this *is* a 4.5! We're all good, people!" With a grin he sticks the plug into the auxiliary line-in. You hear a satisfying click.

fields.Dialogue Text: He furrows his brow as his very large head traces the sublime invisible movement of the music in the very real air of the stuffy tent...
fields.Alternate1: He furrows his brow as his very large head traces the sublime invisible movement of the music in the very real air of the church...

fields.Title: Egg Head: "The young man bobs his head to the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The young man bobs his head to the music, much as before.

fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, isn't it?!" He nods in agreement. "I knew it!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""WHOAH! Culture Cop!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "WHOAH! Culture Cop!"

fields.Dialogue Text: He *seems* sure, but you are left with the nagging doubt you might have overestimated the hard coreness of that jam...

fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't help you with this right now. I need something else, something *extra*..."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Sounds suspiciously like a *question*. I thought the question was: What is the question?"

fields.Title: You: ""So this is the famous van Eyck I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So this is the famous van Eyck I'm hearing?"

fields.Title: You: ""You missed an 'A' there. I yelled..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You missed an 'A' there. I yelled mine with six 'A'-s, so you have to yell it with six too."

fields.Title: You: ""Why is this *Yekokataa* the place..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why is this *Yekokataa* the place to be? What does that mean?"
fields.Alternate1: "You said that before. Why is this *Yekokataa* the place to be? What does that mean?"
fields.Alternate2: "But Yekokataa is a catastrophe zone. A desolate wasteland. It can't be the place to be?"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""We're close!" says the young man w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're close!" says the young man with the tape player and the large boiadeiro boots. Lung-shaped trees sprout on his silver belt buckle.
fields.Alternate1: "We're close!" says the young man standing behind the mixer deck, pumping his fist in the air. Lung-shaped trees grow on his silver belt buckle.

fields.Title: Shivers: "There is a hawthorn tree on Rue de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is a hawthorn tree on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine, right next to the canal. A reel of magnetic tape is caught in its branches, like bronze ribbons blowing in the wind...

fields.Title: You: ""No, I really don't have time for t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I really don't have time for this." (Don't take the task.)

fields.Title: You: ""Good to know.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good to know."

fields.Title: Noid: ""But that's what everybody saw. Exp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But that's what everybody saw. Explain it as you please, but it doesn't really do to just deny it ever happened."

fields.Title: Andre: ""Basically what you need to find he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Basically what you need to find here is a tape with some banging music on it, so that Egg Head could use it to remix van Eyck's jam."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Whooh, hear that?!" He wipes his b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whooh, hear that?!" He wipes his brow. "The sines match perfectly!"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Hey..." Acele looks up from her mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey..." Acele looks up from her microphone. "What did you do to Egg Head, cop-man? Did you *break* him?"

fields.Title: You: ""Just wait and see." (Nod at Egg He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just wait and see." (Nod at Egg Head.)

fields.Title: You: ""It's good you're not a communist a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's good you're not a communist anyway. You should be an ultraliberal."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""But... it needs to be played, on t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But... it needs to be played, on the turntable. And it's broken." Seeing this abuse of music brings a twinge of sadness to his face.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Look around! You gotta help it, he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look around! You gotta help it, help it survive. Can't leave the tune like this." He hands back the bundle of magnetic tape.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""No. No, no, this is gonna make peo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. No, no, this is gonna make people scared!" He hands the tape back to you. "Keep it positive, keep the *love* in the house!"

fields.Title: Acele: ""What is this?" Acele looks up from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is this?" Acele looks up from her contact mic. "It's *good*. How did you guys do that?"
fields.Alternate1: "What is this?" Acele looks up from her contact mic, stunned. "It sounds *so good*. The way melody and bass flow together... how did you make it so perfect?"

fields.Title: You: ""Do what? I just found a random tap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do what? I just found a random tape and brought it to Egg Head. He's just incredibly good at remixing."

fields.Title: You: ""The Horn of Apocalypse. It draweth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Horn of Apocalypse. It draweth near."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Good morning, comrade! Yeaaaaaah!"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good morning, comrade! Yeaaaaaah!" He waves his hand in the air. "Harder core!" The words echo magnificently throughout the nave.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Oscillator matrix?" The man's brow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oscillator matrix?" The man's brow furrows with concern. "Where is that?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "An innocent soul, unaccustomed to a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An innocent soul, unaccustomed to acts of wanton guile.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "A cruel joke to play on an earnest..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cruel joke to play on an earnest torque dork.
fields.Alternate1: A cruel joke to play on a brother torque dork.

fields.Title: Noid: ""That's fucked up, man. Lying like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's fucked up, man. Lying like that. And a cop too..."

fields.Title: You: ""It's only ultra hard core.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's only ultra hard core."

fields.Title: You: ""It's proto -- not hard core at all.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's proto -- not hard core at all."

fields.Title: Noid: "The young man smiles and nods. Slow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The young man smiles and nods. Slowly he picks up two hammers at once.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait! I just remembered something!..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait! I just remembered something! I'm the police!"

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, it's more likely to *hin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, it's more likely to *hinder* us."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""No, this is THE ANSWER!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, this is THE ANSWER!"

fields.Title: You: ""You're just gonna keep saying it's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're just gonna keep saying it's *hard core*, aren't you?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Could there have been a *right* way..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could there have been a *right* way out of this garden of forking paths, you think?

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""It's nice to be important, but it'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's nice to be important, but it's more important to be nice!"

fields.Title: You: ""I was wondering if you knew who ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was wondering if you knew who killed the mercenary hanging behind the Whirling-in-Rags hostel?"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Gotta get the people going!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Gotta get the people going!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Oh, I know! I know this! I can tel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, I know! I know this! I can tell you where it is!"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Like that guy from the pawnshop, wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like that guy from the pawnshop, what was his name? The Bird's Nest Roy.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""NO LIMITS ON THE DANCEFLOOR!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "NO LIMITS ON THE DANCEFLOOR!"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Noid's right, Egg Head's technical..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Noid's right, Egg Head's technical talent is the key.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Something *mysterious* is going on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something *mysterious* is going on here...

fields.Title: You: ""Don't be a fascist... wait, what a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be a fascist... wait, what am I saying? Of course be a fascist!"

fields.Title: You: ""You're wrong. Capital doesn't rule..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're wrong. Capital doesn't rule the nation."

fields.Title: You: ""Welcome to Revachol!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""WELCOME TO REVACHOL! WELCOME TO RE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "WELCOME TO REVACHOL! WELCOME TO REVACHOL! MYSTICAL NATIONHOOD!"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Inside your chest, the heart beats..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Inside your chest, the heart beats still with the after-effects of the sound. Imagine if you could harness that power... making it pulse.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Ooh." His mind is seemingly flippi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ooh." His mind is seemingly flipping through the options. "I don't know. Maybe *someone* can do something with this. I imagine this is the sound that the future could make."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "This is it... this is a new era. Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is it... this is a new era. The fabric of the world has been irrevocably altered.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Welcome to Revachol! Yeaaaaaah!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol! Yeaaaaaah!"

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Isn't that what *real* artists do?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Isn't that what *real* artists do? Make it up as they go along?

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "....as though you're supposed to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ....as though you're supposed to be sharing some tremendous, evangelical secret...

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""There's nothing wrong with it. I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's nothing wrong with it. I'm still in love with the hard core." He turns pensive all of a sudden.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I can be a communist!" He nods. "I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can be a communist!" He nods. "If you want that -- do you want me to be a communist?!"

fields.Title: Noid: ""Please don't turn him into a commu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please don't turn him into a communist."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Yeah! REVACHOL IMPERATIVE!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah! REVACHOL IMPERATIVE!"

fields.Title: You: ""Don't be a communist. That path is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be a communist. That path is *too* hard core."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""HERE COMES THE SUN!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "HERE COMES THE SUN!"

fields.Title: You: ""Superb!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Superb!"

fields.Title: You: ""Alright. Goodbye, Egg Head." [Leav..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. Goodbye, Egg Head." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Andre: ""Uhm, basically, yes it is.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uhm, basically, yes it is."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""YeaaaaaGH!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "YeaaaaaGH!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""True, hard, full core!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "True, hard, full core!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "He feels ashamed he can't be of mor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He feels ashamed he can't be of more service to the future of dance music.

fields.Title: You: ""Before I go on, where is Rue de Sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Before I go on, where is Rue de Saint-Ghislaine?"
fields.Alternate1: "Rue de Saint-Ghislaine... I've been there."

fields.Title: You: ""No, but seriously... I'm a little..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, but seriously... I'm a little worried it isn't."

fields.Title: You: ""Bourgeois love from a bourgeois go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Bourgeois love from a bourgeois god-queen towards a world getting rapidly more bourgeois, that's lungs for you."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Why wouldn't they be? Are the lungs..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why wouldn't they be? Are the lungs not the place where you hold the breath of your soul?

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""THE ADVENT!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE ADVENT!"

fields.Title: Noid: ""I think it's just happenstance. Ch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it's just happenstance. Chaos in action. Contingencies of our limited existence. That and Egg Head's fantastic talent." He nods to his friend behind the turntables.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Wait, they want you to run all the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, they want you to run all the way back to Martinaise with that leg of yours, just to get some 'tape'? Ouch.

fields.Title: You: "Give him a thumbs up."
fields.Dialogue Text: Give him a thumbs up.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I can be an ultra!" He nods. "If y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can be an ultra!" He nods. "If you want that -- do you want me to be an ultra?!"

fields.Title: You: ""You're wrong. The nation can't ben..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're wrong. The nation can't bend all to its will."

fields.Title: Half Light: "The bright future of Revachol refle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The bright future of Revachol reflects off Germaine Egg Head's giant smile. A world of Revacholian domination, where its shores are bereft of ill influence.

fields.Title: You: ""Obviously. One shouldn't get too h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Obviously. One shouldn't get too hasty with their decision-making."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what do you mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what do you mean?"

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, where can I get it repair..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, where can I get it repaired?"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "SIDE-CHAIN THE BEAT!"
fields.Dialogue Text: SIDE-CHAIN THE BEAT!

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Listen, you can use the compressor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Listen, you can use the compressor to select between which track it's compressing, either the auxiliary signal or the main input from the tape. Make it alternate between the signals.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Who will be the innocence of hard-c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who will be the innocence of hard-core anodic dance music?

fields.Title: You: ""Are you a thought reader?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you a thought reader?"

fields.Title: Noid: "The young man picks up a level and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The young man picks up a level and inspects it against the floodlight. The water sparkles in the small measuring tube. "Yes," he says after a while. "I think it's correct to say that."

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I'm sorry.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry."

fields.Title: You: ""I could settle it for you, but not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I could settle it for you, but not right now. Tell me something else, Egg Head."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, I've changed my mind.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I've changed my mind."

fields.Title: You: "Try to think if anything could make..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try to think if anything could make it... harder-core?

fields.Title: You: ""Yeaaaah!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeaaaah!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Good morning, yeah! One, two, thre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good morning, yeah! One, two, three! Yekokataa, the place to be!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""I'm the party boy, it's my job!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm the party boy, it's my job!"

fields.Title: You: ""What is a party boy?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is a party boy?"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""What?!" The young man makes a sudd..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What?!" The young man makes a sudden move, like he's about to turn the volume down. But that would be ridiculous.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Wow, okay! We should start with th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow, okay! We should start with the melody. But where would we get that stuff from?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know. I was thinking *you*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know. I was thinking *you* would know..."

fields.Title: You: ""Really?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Really?"

fields.Title: Logic: "What about that compressor Andre wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What about that compressor Andre was setting up... to achieve some sort of *parallel processing*.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Yeagh, re-mix time!" His voice boo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeagh, re-mix time!" His voice booms through the church as he takes the tape and attaches it to the empty reel slot. "Tape goes here -- into deck B." He clicks a switch, the tape starts spinning...

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Listen, I'm just going to show it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen, I'm just going to show it to you... Ready?"

fields.Title: Andre: ""I was born ready, Egg!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was born ready, Egg!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Oh sure, I can do that!" He nods...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh sure, I can do that!" He nods. "If you want that -- I can avoid taking a stand!"

fields.Title: Noid: ""Please don't turn him into a moral..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please don't turn him into a moralist."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Vibrations thump through your blue..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Vibrations thump through your blue soul. The music sounds much better in the church.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Tape goes around spool. I spin the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tape goes around spool. I spin the world 'round, with my mic in the ground! Yeeaaaahhh!"

fields.Title: You: ""What about this one?" (Give him th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about this one?" (Give him the Smallest Church in Saint-Saëns.)

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""No. No, can't do, this is gonna ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. No, can't do, this is gonna make people sad! This isn't sad-core." He hands the tape back to you.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Wow..." His face lights up with de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow..." His face lights up with delight. "Did you get this from Arno himself?"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Yeah! It was awesome, and scary. V..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah! It was awesome, and scary. Very hard core!" His voice booms through the chamber, then gets silent.

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""Ooh. Ooh!" His puzzled face turns..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ooh. Ooh!" His puzzled face turns into a wicked grin. "But how?!"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Your body is taking a beating from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your body is taking a beating from the low frequencies crashing over you. It's making you feel... alive again.

fields.Title: Egg Head: "The audio assault is glorious. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The audio assault is glorious. The speedfreak dances on the stage, intensely waving his hand in the air.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Isn't something holding it back? From being hyper?" He thinks for a moment, then his expression clears...

fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh yeah, turn him into a communist, c'mon! It would be super!"

fields.Dialogue Text: "ONE MIND! ONE SPIRIT! THERE IS NO OTHER WORLD -- THERE IS NO OTHER LIFE!"

fields.Title: Egg Head: ""COP-MAN!" yells Egg Head."

fields.Title: You: ""Don't be a moralist... wait, what..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be a moralist... wait, what am I saying? You should consider your choice carefully and rationally."

fields.Title: You: ""Andre's got it. Sounds like a loca..."
